
Overview

This is a Flask web application that lets users play a simple game of Blackjack in their browser. The app includes the following features:

Single-player gameplay against a virtual dealer.

A user-friendly interface to hit, stand, and view the game status.

Basic game logic implemented according to standard Blackjack rules.

Features

User-Friendly Interface: Intuitive buttons and game feedback for ease of use.

Dealer Logic: Automated dealer decisions based on game rules.

Session Management: Tracks the game state for each player using Flask sessions.

Requirements

To run this app, you will need:

Python 3.7+

Flask 2.0+

A web browser (for accessing the game)

Usage

Start a new game by visiting the home page.

Use the "Hit" or "Stand" buttons to play your turn.

The dealer will automatically play their turn after you stand.

The game will display the outcome (win, lose, or draw) based on standard Blackjack rules.

Customization

Styling:
You can update static/styles.css to modify the appearance of the app.

Game Logic:
The game rules and logic are implemented in blackjack_logic.py. You can edit this file to adjust or expand the game features.

